            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">While criticism of space tourism is rising, Pop star Katy Perry and five other women embarked on Jeff Bezos’ Blue Origin rocket for an 11-minute space trip. Branded as the first all-female mission in 60 years, they reached over 100km above Earth and crossed the Karman Line, which divides Earth's atmosphere from space. The fully autonomous New Shepard rocket and capsule landed safely in Texas (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-15-04-2025-h1-1-watch-the-entire-trip?source=website" target="_blank">watch the entire trip</a>).</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
        Although the charges for the flight were not revealed, a $150,000 deposit is required to reserve a seat. Blue Origin asserted that the passengers were trained with a focus on physical fitness, emergency protocols, safety measures, and procedures for zero gravity.</p>
        </mj-text>
